references.reason: This paper is foundational for the Graph Contrastive Learning (GCL) approach, a central theme in the target paper, establishing the benchmark for graph self-supervised learning techniques.
GraphMAE is directly compared against in the target paper's experiments, representing a key generative self-supervised learning model whose redundancy is analyzed.
This paper introduces Variational Graph Autoencoders (VGAE), a model type that is relevant to the broader discussion on generative graph self-supervised learning.

This work is crucial as it's one of the earliest successful applications of contrastive learning to graphs, providing a strong theoretical foundation for the target paper's exploration of graph self-supervised learning models.
